@0 = ~Ach!, The ichor on this damned blade nearly burned right through me glove!  Be this sword from the hells themselves?~
@1 = ~Hmm, the hilt on this blade be in rather rough shape, dunnae ye think?  It could be reforged with Githyanki's silver hilt if'n ye could wrestle one away from the beasts.  Mighty dangerous that be, they regard them as a haughty paladin would a holy avenger.  But if'n ye manage to find one, bring it to me, and I'll reforge this caustic carver of yers into something that will strike fear into those blasted mind-flayers.~
@2 = ~Let's see if ye got what I need to reforge that hellish blade of yours...~
@3 = ~Well, let's see what else ye got.~
@4 = ~A corrosive dagger ye got here, eh?  Looks like it's been chewed up and spit out...~
@5 = ~I can fix up this dagger of yers, and make it even more useful as one ye can throw if ye can bring me the Boomerang Dagger +2 to reforge it with.~
@6 = ~Ah, this be the Boomerang Dagger!  A mere 5,000gp and I can get right tae work on fixing up yer corroded dagger.~
@7 = ~What's this? A right nice pair of boots these are, quite soft and quiet.~
@8 = ~I could improve these boots with some liquid mercury and a commission of 7500gp.~
@9 = ~Ah, thats some liquid mercury alright, I can improve these boots with them.~
@10 = ~What've ye got here?  Hah! a crown of false gemstones and gold.  Still, it seems to have a bit o' enchantment to it...~
@11 = ~I could refit this lying crown of yers with enchanted ioun stones to improve it.  Obsidian, lavendar, clear, and scarlet/blue would do the trick.~
@12 = ~These looks to be the stones I need.  If'n ye can part with a mere 5,000gp, I can reforge that crown of yours into one fit for a king if ye'd like.~
@13 = ~Blessed be!  A fine dwarven helm bearing the mark of Dumathoin!~
@14 = ~All I would need are some good horns, and 5,000gp and I can make the glory of Dumathoin really shine from this helm.~
@15 = ~These horns will do nicely, I can use these to make that dwarven helm of yours into something Dumathoin himself would be proud to wear.~
@16 = ~Hmm, an amulet made of petrified eyes?  Cannae say I've ever seen anything of the like.~
@17 = ~I might be able to make these old eyes see further with a scroll of farsight, wizard eye, a couple of potions of perception, and 5,000gp.~
@18 = ~Here we are, the scrolls and potions I need to enhanced those blind eyes on your amulet.~
@19 = ~This be a nice belt o' skill you have here, Keenedge's work if'n I'm not mistaken.~
@20 = ~Ol' Cromwell can make this belt even better for ye, I just need some gauntlets of weapon skill and expertise along with a scroll of distintegrate to transfer the magics and 10,000gp for the work.~
@21 = ~Ye got the gauntlets and scroll, I can get to work on improving Sa'yan's belt for ye if'n ye want.~
@22 = ~Nice sharp throwing dart ye have here, I almost pricked me fingers on it.~
@23 = ~I can improve this bloody dart of yours with five scrolls of melf's acid arrow, five sphene gems, and 5,000gp.~
@24 = ~Lemme see, ye got the five scrolls and sphene gems, I can get right to work on that dart for ya if'n ye want.~
@25 = ~Bloody hells!  Just touching this blade's hilt makes me feel as weak as a young lass!~
@26 = ~I cannae enhance this blade unless ye finds me a skull of dark power, mayhap a lich's.  And I would need 15,000gp for me trouble.~
@27 = ~I'll be a basilisk's lunch, that be a dark skull from a lich alright.  I can use it to enhance that black blade of yours.~
@28 = ~Bloody hells!  Just touching this hammer's haft makes me feel as weak as a young lass!~
@29 = ~I cannae enhance this hammer unless ye finds me a skull of dark power, mayhap a lich's.  And I would need 15,000gp for me trouble.~
@30 = ~I'll be a basilisk's lunch, that be a dark skull from a lich alright.  I can use it to enhance that black hammer of yours.~
@31 = ~What's this 'ere?  Some spoony bard's hat?~
@32 = ~I can make this pretentious hat more practical for a minstrel with ioun stones of gold and dusty rose.  Toss in 7,500gp for the day's work and Cromwell will do ye right.~
@33 = ~Aye, ioun stones of both gold and dusty rose ye have here, I can get to work on that musician's hat o' yours if ye would like.~
@34 = ~What've ye got there, a Thayvian mage's robe?~
@35 = ~If'n ye happen to come across the robe of vecna, I can use its threading and magics to enhance that flamin' conjurer's robe of yours.  It would cost ye 10,000gp for the commission.~
@36 = ~I see ye've managed to get the old lich's robe, quite impressive.  I can use it to improve that Thayvian robe if'n ye want.~
@37 = ~What's this now?  One of the bucklers from those mercenaries at Baldur's Gate?~
@38 = ~This old dwarf can rework that Flaming Fist buckler of yours into something special if'n ye can provide me with a reflection shield +1, two scrolls of protection against normal missiles, two potions of mirrored eyes, and 10,000gp for me trouble.~
@39 = ~Ye've got the reflection shield, scrolls, and potions.  I can rework that Flaming Fist buckler of yours if'n ye would like.~
@40 = ~Is this?.... Hah!  It is!  The false "Crom Faeyr".  Where in the realms did you find this accursed thing?~
@41 = ~Hmmm, I might be able to improve that accursed hammer if'n you can find me a rune of clangeddin to scribe into it.  It would take 5,000gp fer the work.~
@42 = ~This be one of the clangeddin runes alright, I can use it to enhance that blasphemous hammer of yours.~
@43 = ~What've ye here?  The balance and heft of this burning blade be all wrong, was it even made to be held by mortal hands?~
@44 = ~I can reforge that unbalanced flamin' blade of yours, and make it a far more effective and balanced weapon.  I would just need a sword of flame, a blade of searing, and five scrolls of agannazar's scorcher.  7,500gp for the day's work at the forge and it'd be a done deal for ye.~
@45 = ~A flaming sword, a searing blade, and five of the scorcher scrolls.  I can get right to work on reforging that unweildy burning sword of yours if ye'd like.~
@46 = ~Ahhh, just lookin' at these boots reminds me of gazin' at the skies over the harbor at night.~
@47 = ~If'n ye want me to improve Crommus' old boots for ye, I'd need a few things.  Two potions each of magic protection, magic shielding, and magic blocking.~
@48 = ~Ye have all the potions I need here to reforge those starry boots, I would just need 5,000gp for me work at the forge.  Shall I get started on em for ye?~
@49 = ~Placeholder~
@50 = ~Ahh, I believe I recognize the craftmanship of this green dragonscale o' yers.  Jegg's work is it?  How is the ol' bird?~
@51 = ~I can rework this dragonscale into better armor if ye can bring me some red or shadow dragon scales.~
@52 = ~Aye, ye've collected some more scales from the dastardly beasts.  I can use 'em to reforge yer green dragonscale.~
@53 = ~I can use these red dragon scales to reforge the green dragonscale into lightweight scale armor or a suit of heavy plate.~
@54 = ~What've ye here, scales from a toxic green dragon?  Ach, the smell is enough to knock a buzzard off a gut-wagon.~
@55 = ~I can use these noxious scales to make for ye a lightweight suit of scale armor, a suit of heavy plate armor, a protective helmet, or even a sturdy shield.~
@56 = ~It'll cost ye 5,000gp and a day's worth of yer sweat helping at me forge.~
@57 = ~I can use these shadow dragon scales to reforge the green dragonscale into a lightweight scale armor, or a suit of heavy plate.~
@58 = ~Scales from a shadow dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@59 = ~This be a nice greatsword ye have here, a dragon's gift?  She looks rather worn...~
@60 = ~I can use either these red dragon scales or shadow dragon scales to reforge yer green dragonscale into lightweight scale armor or a suit of heavy plate.~
@61 = ~It'll cost ye 15,000 gold and since me apprentice would rather chase harlots and courtesans than work, ye'll need to stay on a day and help me run the forge.~
@62 = ~Well, let's see what else ye've got then.~
@63 = ~I can reforge this blade, I would just need a sharp new blade for the forgin'.  A Githyanki's vorpal blade of silver would work best.~
@64 = ~Ahh yes, this be a vorpal blade alright, I can use it to reforge that dragon's sword of yours, along with 7,500 gold for me trouble.~
@65 = ~The Verdant Crimson Dragon Plate?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@66 = ~I can rework the armor for ye with some more dragon scales.  Any color from the scaly bastards will do.~
@67 = ~Scales from a shadow dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@68 = ~Ye would like to enhance that silver dragon's blade of yers further, ye say?~
@69 = ~Scales from a white dragon? I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@70 = ~Scales from a dragon of noble silver?  It saddens this old dwarf to know such a majestic creature fell for these scales.  I cannae let this creature's death be in vain, I can use these to improve your armor.~
@71 = ~Enhancing your silver dragon further blade be a tall order, I'd need an elemental gemstone for it, and 10,000gp to fit it to your sword.~
@72 = ~Scales from a blue dragon?  I can use these to enhance your armor.~
@73 = ~Looks like ye have an elemental gem of frost here, I can use this to enhance your dragon blade with.~
@74 = ~It'll cost ye 20,000 gold, and since me apprentice has ran off to Waterdeep with a rather homely courtesan, I'll need yer help at the forge once again.~
@75 = ~I can use these dragon scales to enhance your dragonscale armor with.~
@76 = ~Fancy yerself a dragonslayer, do ye?  I can use any of these scales to enhance your dragonscale armor with.~
@77 = ~The Verdant Shadow Dragonscale?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@78 = ~I can rework the armor for ye with some more scales.  Blue, white, red, or silver will do.~
@79 = ~Scales from a red dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@80 = ~Well now, I haven't seen any of these in an age... be these a pair of stalker's gauntlets?~
@81 = ~Always wanted to try me hand at reforgin a pair o' these, and I believe I can do it for ye with a bracers of blinding strike, an improved haste scroll, two potions of power and two potions of master thievery.~
@82 = ~Ye have everything I need here to upgrade those stalker gauntlets of yers.  It'll be 10,000gp and I'll need yer help at me forge.  Me son of a kobald of an apprentice was out all hours deep in his cups with the blasted courtesans again.~
@83 = ~The Scorched Earth again eh?  Not hot enough for ye?  Heh.~
@84 = ~Be a difficult task to make this blade burn hotter... but I might just be able to do it for ye if'n ye can find me an elemental gem of flame.  Oh, and a small commission for me work, 15,000gp should cover it.  And lest I forget, I'll need yer help for the day at me forge.  That damnable apprentice of mine has gone and knocked up a half-orc lass.  I doubt I will ever see him again, heh.~
@85 = ~Looks like ye found an elemental gem of flame, they be rare as hen's teeth.  Shall we get started on mounting it into yer blade?~
@86 = ~What've ye got here?  A lucky belt ye say?~
@87 = ~Methinks I can make this belt even more "lucky" for ye and yer friends with five scrolls of luck and 10,000gp.~
@88 = ~Ye have everything I need to fix up that lucky belt for ye, I'll just need yer help at the forge again.  That half orc lass did a real number on me apprentice, he's going to be laid up a few days at least, the scoundrel.  Shall we begin?~
@89 = ~Now this is an odd bird, a cursed staff that's uncursed...but still cursed?~
@90 = ~I may just be able to empower that accursed stick o' yers a bit.  I would need a wand of fire, a wand of frost, and 5,000gp.~
@91 = ~Aye, ye got the wands I need here for the uncursed staff.  Would ye like me to do the work?  As much as I hate ta ask, I'll need yer help again.   My apprentice be at the temple with the half-orc lass, she be makin' an honest man o' him whether he want it or not, ha!~
@92 = ~Ahh, yer accursed stick again, ye would like to have it recharged ye say?~
@93 = ~Ol' Cromwell might be able to work some more magic into that old stick with another wand of fire, a wand of frost, and another 5,000gp for me trouble.~
@94 = ~Ye have another wand of fire and frost here too, shall we get to work?  Me apprentice is away on his honeymoon with the half-orc lass at the Low Lantern in Baldur's Gate, I'll need ye to help me again.~
@95 = ~Ahh, ye've got an old backwhacker here, I could use one of these for me bastard apprentice.  Just to keep 'im in line o' course.~
@96 = ~If'n ye come accross a wyvern tail and a gnasher club, I can reforge this backwhacker into a really nasty implement for a rogue.  I'd just need a mere 5,000gp for me trouble.~
@97 = ~Ye've got the wyvern tail and gnasher.  Ye ready to get started on the whacker?  Just one day's worth of yer help at me forge again if'n ye can.  Me apprentice is nursing a hangover he says, Pfft.~
@98 = ~Hmm, be this bow of orcish origin?  Looks to be quite frightening.~
@99 = ~I can make this banshee's bow wail upon your enemies for you, I would just need something like some screaming bagpipes to make it do so, along with a bowstring of gesen or gond to hold it all together.~
@100 = ~I would need 10,000gp and yer help fer the day.  Me apprentice managed to smash his hand with me anvil and will be laid up fer awhile.~
@101 = ~I can use this silver hilt to reforge that devil's sword if ye would like, it would cost ye 10,000 gold fer the work.~
@102 = ~deprecated~
@103 = ~deprecated~
@104 = ~It doesn't look like ye have what I need to reforge that hellblade...~
@105 = ~Let's see if ye got all I need to rework this orcish bow...~ 
@106 = ~I can use this gesen bowstring along with yer bagpipes to improve your bow.~
@107 = ~I can use this bowstring of gond along with yer bagpipes to improve your bow.~
@108 = ~Quite the adventurer you must be to have bowstrings from gond and gesen.~
@109 = ~Ye have some of the parts here, but I'll need the screaming pipes along with one of the gond or gesen bowstrings to complete the work.~
@110 = ~I'd need 10,000gp and yer help fer the day at me forge.  That idiot Duergar apprentice of mine is down at the docks fishing again.  Fishing for harlots is what he really be doin', I wager.~
@111 = ~Nice gloves ye got here, just in me size too!~
@112 = ~I can reforge these gloves for ye and make them a better fit too with some extra materials. Mayhap some bracers of archery, a bracers of defense AC3, some gloves of pickpocketing and 5,000gp for the stitchwork.~
@113 = ~Looks like ye got all the materials I need to reforge yer doeskin gloves, Ye up for another day o' work with me at me shop?~
@114 = ~What've ye here....a blackened arrow that seems to sap the strength right from me arm...~
@115 = ~I can make ye more of these arrows, mayhap even an unlimited supply with the right components.  I would just need on of yer arrows, a quiver of plenty +2 and 5,000 gold.~
@116 = ~I can use this quiver of plenty +2 to make an unlimited supply of these darkness arrows for ye, I just need 5,000 gold and yer help at me forge for the day.~
@117 = ~What've ye here....a blackened bullet that seems to sap the strength right from me arm...~
@118 = ~I can make ye more of these bullets, mayhap even an unlimited supply with the right components.  I would just need one of yer bullets, a bag of plenty +2 and 5,000 gold.~
@119 = ~I can use this bag of plenty +2 to make an unlimited supply of these darkness bullets for ye, I just need 5,000 gold and yer help at me forge for the day.~
@120 = ~Ahh, this be a rather nice old wizard's cloak ye got here.~
@121 = ~I can reforge this cloak for ye into something really special for the aracnially-inclined, I'll just need an amulet of metaspell influence to make a new clasp, and a cloak of displacement for a new lining.  I'll also need yer help fer the day at me forge.~
@122 = ~Ye have the cloak I need fer the lining, and the metaspell amulet for a new clasp.  5,000gp and we can get started.~
@123 = ~Hmmm, very nice dagger ye got here, imbued with all the elements at once?~
@124 = ~Ye know, this dagger o' yers would be much more useful if'n ye could throw it.  I could improve it as such with a boomerang dagger and 5,000gp fer the forgin'.~
@125 = ~Ye have a boomerang dagger here, I can use it to enhance that elemental dagger.  Me apprentice didn't show up again today, so I will need yer help fer the day.~
@126 = ~Ah, the elemental dagger again, ye want it further enhanced?~
@127 = ~Enhancing this elemental dagger is a tall order, ye would need to find me an elemental gem to use with it.~
@128 = ~I can use the Soul of Frost to enhance yer elemental dagger, I just need 5,000gp and yer help at the forge.~
@129 = ~Ach!  Ye should warn a dwarf before ye hand him a blasted pike that shocks ye!~
@130 = ~I could reforge the storm pike if'n ye find me a wave shaft to work with.~
@131 = ~Aye, this be the haft of the bitch-queens' weapon.  I can use it to reforge the storm pike into a throwing axe or a halberd for ye.~
@132 = ~I would need the wave shaft and 7,500gp.  Oh, and lest I forget, I'll need yer help at the forge again, me apprentice was found dead in the sewers with a courtesan's heel stuck in his back.~
@133 = ~The maelstrom axe?  Aye, I can enhance it further for ye.~
@134 = ~I would need the hammer of thunderbolts +3 along with the scroll of crom faeyr, and 10,000gp for me work to enhance the maelstrom axe.~
@135 = ~Ye have the hammer of thunderbolts and the scroll, I can reforge yer axe with these.~
@136 = ~The maelstrom pike?  Aye, I can enhance it further for ye.~
@137 = ~I would need the wave blade, and the scroll of crom faeyr, and 10,000gp for me work to enhance the maelstrom pike?~
@138 = ~Ye have the wave blade and the scroll, I can reforge the pike with these.~
@139 = ~Aye, what's this?  An ioun stone of magiked troll's blood?  Smells worse than me apprentice after a night at the tavern with well-loved harlots.~
@140 = ~I could reforge this inoun stone for ye, it needs a warrior's spirit to focus the power inside.  If'n ye can somehow find a pale green ioun stone in yer travels, I could use it, along with five scrolls of resist fear, and five potions of regeneration, and five potions of heroism to enhance yer ioun stone.~
@141 = ~This be the pale green stone I need, the potions and the scrolls.  Toss in 5,000gp for me coffers and I'll get to work for ye.~
@142 = ~Ye want me to further enhance the trollkiller ioun stone?~
@143 = ~It be a tall order to enhance the trollkiller stone further, I'd need another green ioun stone with a warrior's fighting spirit, and another 5,000gp for the forgin'.~
@144 = ~This be a green stone with another fighter's spirit inside alright.  Shall we get started on using it to enahnce yer trollkiller stone?~
@145 = ~A shield from the Egons?  Looks like it's seen better days, friend.~
@146 = ~Cromwell can reforge it for ye, I would need another shield to rework it with, such as a shield of the lost +2, and would need some illithium ore for the finish.~
@147 = ~Aye, I can work with this ore and shield.  7,500gp for the commission and I can get started right away for ye.~
@148 = ~What've ye brought for me today?  Looks to be a shortblade with some rather sharp scales for an edge.~
@149 = ~To further improve this blade for ye, I would need a heart of the damned and 7,500gp.~
@150 = ~Ye have the heart here, and the gold, I'll just need yer help at me forge again for the day, me apprentice took one hell of a beatin from a sailor at the tavern last eve.~
@151 = ~Ahh, the bulwark of egons, ye wish it improved further ye say?~
@152 = ~I can improve yer shield with an old symbol of the sun god, Amaunator, if ye find one, bring it back here and I'll fix up yer shield for a meager 5,000gp.~
@153 = ~The symbol of Amaunator!  I can use this to improve yer bulwark of egons.  Shall we get to work on 'er?~
@154 = ~This be one heavenly crossbow ye got here, ye wish it enhanced eh?~
@155 = ~I could enhance this bow for ye, I would need something to make a new limb with, say a gesen bowshaft.  And I would need 5,000 fer me trouble.~
@156 = ~This be gesen's work alright, I can use this to enhance yer crossbow.~
@157 = ~Interesting find ye have here, an ethereal spear of sorts?~
@158 = ~I could reforge this shadowed spear of yers into something special, I would need ye to bring me an elemental gem.~
@159 = ~I'll be... an elemental gem of wind, I can use this to enhance that shadowy spear of yers.  I just need 7,500gp and yer help at me forge.~
@160 = ~Ye want the Shadowed Spear of the Tempest enhanced further ye say?~
@161 = ~I could do the reforgin, I'd need a new head for the spear.  Ixil's spike would do the trick if'n ye can find it.~
@162 = ~Ye have Ixil's spike here, I can use this to reforge yer spear.  I would need another 7,500gp and a day at the forge.~
@163 = ~Scales from a green dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@164 = ~Ye say ye would like yer Dragonscale Shield made sturdier?~
@165 = ~Hmmm, it would take some extremely tough scales to improve this shield, only some from a black dragon would work.~
@166 = ~Ye certainly are a brave one to have slain a black dragon for these scales.  I can use these to enhance yer shield.  I would need 7,500gp fer the commission, shall we begin work?~
@167 = ~Ye would like to improve the Tongue of Acid even further?~
@168 = ~It be a tall order to improve that hellblade more, I'd need to reforge it using an elemental gemstone and it would take 15,000gp fer my work at the forge.~
@169 = ~By the Soul Forger, an elemental gem of corrosive ichor?  Never thought I'd see such a thing in me lifetime.  I can use this to reforge yer hellblade.  I would just need 15,000gp and yer help at me forge again.~
@170 = ~Ey, whats this?  Appears to be Iriaeborian craftsmanship that forged this armor.~
@171 = ~I could greatly improve the protective ability of this shadowy rogue's gear.  If'n ye are able to bring down a grand drake of the shadows, bring me some of it's scales.~
@172 = ~Ye've gone and slain a big, dark, lizard 'ave ye?  These scales will do nicely for your Iriaeborian leathers.   Just a toss 7,500gp in fer me coffers and I'll get to work for ye.~
@173 = ~Ey?  What be this?  Some accursed bard's bracers?~
@174 = ~Hmmm, ye know, ol' Cromwell may be able to make these jokers' bracers better for ye.  It'd take some dark magic though.  I'd need to use the power from two demon's hearts along with 5,000gp fer me trouble, and I cannae gaurantee the curse would be lifted.~
@175 = ~Well now, ye've gone and carved two hearts from demons.  I'll not ask ye where from, but if'n ye would like me to use em to enhance those bracers of yers, I'll get to work right away.~
@176 = ~Ye have a blessed ring here, do ye?  Did ye pluck this one from Strohm's tomb?  I cannae hardly believe me eyes.~
@177 = ~I can improve this holy ring fer ya with an equally holy gemstone, such as the Eye of Tyr.~
@178 = ~Ah, yes indeed, this be the Eye of Tyr, I can use this to improve the ring of purity.  I just need 5,000gp and a day at the forge for the work.~
@179 = ~A Calimshite saber?  Nicely balanced and quick, ye would like it improved?~
@180 = ~I can reforge this blade if ye can bring me another fast saber, like the Belm +2, and a murky oil of speed to temper it with.~
@181 = ~Ye have the Belm +2 and the oil I need to reforge this blade for you, just 5,000gp fer me work and it's a done deal.~
@182 = ~Hmm, very interesting blade ye have here, dark as night, cold to the touch and seems to seethe with the anger of unfulfilled purpose.  Appears to be a sharran ceremonial blade with a lot of age to it, aye?~
@183 = ~Aye, I can enhance this blade for ye.  A gemstone of focused dark energy would empower this dark sword for ye if If mounted in place of the ceremonial stone in the crossguard.~
@184 = ~Let me rummage through yer pack and see if ye have something I can use to enhance this dark blade for ye...~
@185 = ~Hmm, what's this?  A stone ye retrieved from a powerful fiend of darkest shadow eh?  I can use this to enhance that dead priestess' blade of yours.~
@186 = ~Deprecated~
@187 = ~Deprecated~
@188 = ~I would just need the stone and 5,000gp for the commission to do the work.~
@189 = ~Deprecated~
@190 = ~Ah, blade of the dark moon goddess?  Ye wish it further enhanced?~
@191 = ~*ponders while stroking his beard*

Aye, it certainly be possible, the blade be good enough, but this ceremonial hilt is what be holding 'er back.  If ye can find and bring me a hilt suitable for such a dark blade, I can reforge it for ye.~
@192 = ~This certainly be a unique hilt ye have here, and I can feel the dark energies within.  Aye, this will work for Varscona's reforgin'.  I would just need 10,000gp for the work and yer help for the day once again at me forge, since I cannae rely on that rat-bastard apprentice.  I should have known better than to take that Duergar under me wing.~
@193 = ~It cannae be.... a magical axe from the lost Stonfire clan!  It was here in Athkatla in some blasted tavern, ye say?~
@194 = ~It'd be a right honor to enhance this fine piece o' dwarven craftsmanship for ye.  To do so would take nothing less than an elemental gemstone of flame and 10,000 gold crowns.~
@195 = ~Aye, this is certainly a gemstone of flame ye have here, shall we get to work on yer axe?~
@196 = ~Ah, this looks to be some scrappy ol' wizard's hat...~
@197 = ~If'n ye would like to have this old hat enhanced, it'd take some potent magics.  Methinks it would take the Circlet of Netheril, nothing less.~
@198 = ~Aye, this be the Cirlet of Netheril ye have here.  I can enhance that old pointy hat of yers with it along with a mere 10,000 gold crowns fer me trouble at tha' forge~
@199 = ~The Sourcerer's Cap?  Ye say ye would like it enhanced further?  Hmmm, let me think a moment...~
@200 = ~Yes, I believe I can enhance this cap o' yers.  I would need an ioun stone of bronze and 5,000 gold crowns~
@201 = ~Well then, ye certainly be proficient in the adventurin' business.  I can use this bronze ioun stone to enhance yer Sourcerer's Cap.  Are ye ready to help at me forge fer the day, <CHARNAME>?~
@202 = ~What be this? looks to be an unfinished garment constructed of human skin?  I'll not ask ye where ye got this from.~
@203 = ~With the right components, I could finish this ghastly thing into a completely serviceable piece of armor.  If ye are able to pry Vecna's robes from Ribald's greedy fingers, and find me some blood from a shadow dragon, I could finish the work.~
@204 = ~This be the old Lich's robe sure enough, and by the Soul Forger... is this murky vial filled with the life-blood from a Shadow Drake?  Such a sight to behold, it's almost as if this be bled from the very void itself.  With these, and a generous contribution of 10,000 gold crowns for the forgin' I will get to work on that fleshy garment for ye right away.~
@205 = ~Ye say ye would like the Lich's Raiment improved even further?  This be a tall order, even for me...~
@206 = ~I cannae make this armor any more powerful without an equally powerful artifact of dark magick.  If'n ye can somehow find an intact Lich's skull, I might be able to do something with it.~
@207 = ~Ye never cease to amaze this old dwarf.  How in the nine hells did ye come across this skull?  Never ye mind, it's not important.  If ye can suffer the loss of 10,000 more gold crowns, I can use this skull to improve that ghoulish mage armor of yers.~
@208 = ~What's this now? Some dusty old parchment?  Ah, ye have quite the find here friend, 'tis a majick-locked scroll, likely containing something special, eh?~
@209 = ~Me granda taught me a thing or two about these scrolls, and I can remove the seal for ye.  It requires meticulous tracing of the cantrip with dragon's blood from a steady hand.  Blood from any dragon will do the trick, but I have to tell ye, I cannae guarantee the same result twice, just the nature of such a seal, I'm afraid.~
@210 = ~Aye, ye've brought me some blood from those overgrown lizards.  I can use this in unsealing that scroll of yers.~
@211 = ~I can use this dragon's blood to unseal that scroll...~
@212 = ~I can use this shadow dragon's blood to unseal that scroll...~
@213 = ~I can use this silver dragon's blood to unseal that scroll...~
@214 = ~deprecated~
@215 = ~deprecated~
@216 = ~*spits in disgust at the sight of the vials of dragon's blood*

  Good riddiance to those scaly bastards, my dragonslayer friend.  I can use any of these vials of wyrm vitae to remove the seal on that scroll.~
@217 = ~In addition to the blood, I will need a sum 5,000 gold crowns for me time in removing the seal on yer old scroll.~
@218 = ~deprecated~
@219 = ~What's this ye've here?  Looks to be a Kara-Turan blade, but....doesn't appear to be forged by mortal hands....~
@220 = ~Ye say ye would like this blade improved?  Aye, I can do it, but I'll need something special.  If'n ye can find me a a gemstone of light, I can use it to rework that crimson blade.~
@221 = ~A gemstone of pure light.... rather impressive ye be in the art of adventurin'.  With this and 5,000 gold pieces, I can reforge yer blade.~
@222 = ~Ah, ye've got a nicely balanced old fighter's blade here, seen alot of use.... ye would like it reforged?~
@223 = ~Aye, I can reforge this blade for ye, I would need something to give it a bit more pep... a gemstone of light would to the trick.~
@224 = ~This be a gemstone of brilliant light alright, I can use this to reforge that fighter's blade of yours, it would set ye back a mere 5,000 gold coins and a day's worth of yer help at me forge.~
@225 = ~Ah, the Kara-Turan blade of legend again, eh?  Ye say ye would like it enhanced further?~
@226 = ~Aye, I can enhance it, but an unearthly blade requires unearthly ore to reforge.  Nothing less than starfall ore would do the trick.~
@227 = ~This ore certainly be of unearthly origin, I can use this to reforge that red katana of yours.  A simple 10,000 golden coins from your coffers would seal the deal.~
@228 = ~The Severance +3?  A blade this well balanced be tough to enhance any further....~
@229 = ~If'n ye can somehow find me some ore from the heavens, I can reforge yer blade with it.~
@230 = ~Aye, this be ore from the stars alright, I can use it to enhance that old fighter's blade of yers.  I would just need 10,000 gold pieces and a day's worth of yer help at me forge.~
@231 = ~What's this now? Some scales from a black dragon?  Good on ye fer stickin' the wicked beast.~
@232 = ~These be some impressively tough scales, I can make ye a lightweight suit of scale armor, a suit of heavy plate, a protective helmet, or even a sturdy shield with these.~
@233 = ~Scales from a black dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@234 = ~The Verdant Crimson Dragonscale?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@235 = ~The Verdant Shadow Dragon Plate?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@236 = ~What've ye here?  A morningstar forged by an Ilmateran priest?  Surely to be blessed by the crying god himself, eh?~
@237 = ~Aye, I can improve it for ye.  I would need a gemstone fitting for the crying god, a king's tear, and a scroll of champion's strength to empower it.~
@238 = ~Ah, this be a tear of kings alright, and the champion's strength scroll as well.  I can get to work on that morningstar for ye right away, if'n ye can part with a mere 3,000gp for the work.~
@239 = ~Ilusarian's blessed morningstar again eh?  Ye wish it further enhanced?~
@240 = ~It be a challenge to improve it further, but me granda would surely strike at me from the grave if'n I could'nt, hah!  If ye come across a crystallized tear from a nymph in yer travels, I can use it to enhance yer morningstar.~
@241 = ~A crystallized nymph's tear... rarer than hen's teeth, but sure enough, ye have one here.  If ye can part with a mere 5,000 gold, I can get to work on fitting it to yer morningstar.~
@242 = ~Hmmm, a ring of oak?  Seems to have a bit 'o enchantment to it, but needs a stone set in 'er to be complete.~
@243 = ~I can complete this oaken ring of yers if'n ye can find me an elemental gemstone, or a Nymph's Tear to set into it.~
@244 = ~Ahh, it appears ye have a gem here I can use for yer oaken ring.~
@245 = ~I can use the Heart of Flame to complete your oaken ring.~
@246 = ~I can use the Breath of Wind to complete your oaken ring.~
@247 = ~I can use the Eye of Ichor to complete your oaken ring.~
@248 = ~I can use the Soul of Frost to complete your oaken ring.~
@249 = ~Ye must have a miner's spirit in ye to have found stones such as these, I can use any of them to complete yer oaken ring.~
@250 = ~It'll take a day's worth of your help at me forge, and a mere 5,000 gold for the commission.~
@251 = ~What've ye here now?  Looks to be one of those enchanted crossbow bolts I heard about from the battle at Dragonspear.   Talk around the docks is there be a surplus of these from the war that found their way to Athkatla.  Bloodscalp's work I'd wager, heh.~
@252 = ~Ye want these enhanced?  Tymora be your lady <CHARNAME>, I've been wanting to get me mitts on these new bolts and work with 'em.  If'n ye can find and bring me no less than forty each of bolts of fire +1 and bolts of ice +1, I can reforge them into something more potent.~
@253 = ~Aye, ye've enough bolts here for me to work with.  If ye can part with 1,000 gold crowns, I'll get to work on 'em right away.~
@254 = ~What be this ye have here?  Looks to be a shell from a remorhaz, pretty rare in these parts to be sure.~
@255 = ~Taerom once told me about a rather impressive helm he made from one of these shells.  I could make for ye such a helm, may even save yer hide if ye get into a scrap with some of those cowled wizards, heh.  6,000 gold coins be the cost for the work, what say ye?~
@256 = ~Now then, this certainly be a unique piece ye have here, a cursed blade from the Abyss, is it?  If'n I didn't know better, I'd say ye went and accepted a gift from some devil and reaped the rewards, heh!~
@257 = ~Aye, I believe I can repair this abyssal blade for ye, would take some special ore though.  I'd need some abyssal bloodiron to reforge the broken blade, and a scroll of remove curse to lift the curse the hell-beast placed on it, else the blade would just break again.~
@258 = ~This be the ore alright, and ye've the scroll as well.  Now just the matter of my commission.  5,000 gold and I'll forge ye a blade guaranteed never to break again.~
@259 = ~Ye wish more power from your bloodiron blade ye say?~
@260 = ~*ponders for a moment.........*

Aye, I believe I can do it, but I will need the infernal blood of a demon lord, nothing less.  If ye can manage to wrest some from one of the hell-beasts, bring it to me and we can use it to temper yer blade.~
@261 = ~Ye have some blood from a demon lord?  Well then, ye certainly be a fearless one, <CHARNAME>.  If'n ye can manage to part with 10,000 gold for the work, I'll get started on 'er.~
@262 = ~The reforged demon's gift?  Ye would like even more power from it, aye?~
@263 = ~*bellows in laughter*

<CHARNAME>, there are limits to even what ol' Cromwell can do.  Empowering this damned blade any further would take something on the order of magnitude of an eye from the demon prince himself!~
@264 = ~*stares in disbelief for a moment.......*

By the Soul Forger!!! I see it but I still cannae believe it.....  An eye from the Demogorgon!~
@265 = ~<CHARNAME>, I would be honored to set this eye in your demon's blade.  This be on the house, nay any commission required.  Once word gets out that this dwarf forged an artifact from the demon prince's eye, my forge will be worked non-stop till the end of me days to be certain.~
@266 = ~A shame it be.  I'll be here if'n ye change yer mind.~
@267 = ~Ah, the Sharran priestess' blade.  Has it been serving ye well enough?  No?  Ye wish it more powerful?  Hmmmmm... 

*spins his hammer in one hand while pondering*

.......aye, it may be possible to enhance further.~
@268 = ~I wager that If'n ye can find a gemstone of shadow, one imbued with energies from the Shadow Plane, the new hilt would accept it as a pommel stone and bring it to it's fullest potential.  I've nary an idea where ye would find such a thing though, maybe in the very plane of shadows itself.~
@269 = ~*closely inspects the Imbued Shadow Gem*

Aye, this'll do for a pommel gem, I can feel the presence of shadow just holding this stone.  I'll need 7,500 gold crowns fer tha' work, and I can get started right away if ye wish.~
@270 = ~.~
@271 = ~.~
@272 = ~.~
@273 = ~Ah, looks like ye may have a stone of two here I can use.~
@274 = ~Ah, the Heart of Flame.  I can use this to enhance this dagger o' yers.~
@275 = ~Ah, the Eye of Ichor.  I can use this to enhance this dagger o' yers.~
@276 = ~Ah, the Breath of Wind.  I can use this to enhance this dagger o' yers.~
@277 = ~Ah, the Soul of Frost.  I can use this to enhance this dagger o' yers.~
@278 = ~Ye've gone and found some elemental gems, I can use any of these to enhance yer dagger.~
@279 = ~Ye say ye would like the Maelstrom Axe further empowered?~
@280 = ~Aye, it be simple enough work, but I'd need an elemental gemstone of water to coax it out of 'er.~
@281 = ~This be an elemental gem of water, sure enough.  I can use this to enhance yer hand axe.  If'n ye can part with 7,500 gold crowns, I'll get started right away.~
@282 = ~Ye say ye would like the Maelstrom Pike further empowered?~
@283 = ~This be an elemental gem of water, sure enough.  I can use this to enhance yer halberd.  If'n ye can part with 7,500 gold crowns, I'll get started right away.~
@284 = ~I can use the Body of Water to complete your oaken ring.~
@285 = ~This be a nice enough scimitar ye have here, well balanced, and the magnificent sheen of the blade ia akin to sunrise over the sea...  Ye say you would like it enhanced?~
@286 = ~Aye, it can certainly be done, keep a keen eye towards an elemental gemstone in yer travels, specifically one of water.  Bring that, and 7,500 gold coins back to me forge, and I'll fix that blade up right-quick.~
@287 = ~This be the gemstone I need, sure enough.  And ye've the gold as well.  Shall we get started?~
@288 = ~Hmmmm, nice, bright shield ye got here.  Blessed by the Morninglord is it?~
@289 = ~It can be improved, aye, with the right components.  I believe we can make this shield shine like the very sun itself if you can bring me a holy symbol of the forgotten Amaunator.~
@290 = ~Ah, this is most certainly a holy symbol of the old sun god.  I would just need 3,500 gold fer the commission, and the help of your sword-arm for a day at me forge to rework your shield.~
@291 = ~Your calmishite saber?  Aye, I believe I can enhance it further for ye.~
@292 = ~I can make this speedy saber burn through foes even faster with an elemental gemstone of fire.  If'n ye come across one while spelunkin' ruins or some such, bring it back to me shop.~
@293 = ~This is an elemental gemstone of fire alright, I can use this to enhance yer saber.  It would cost ye 7,500gp for me efforts.~
@294 = ~Ahh, now this holy blade be a rare piece indeed, my friend.  I've heard tales of a lass weilding a sword like this at Dragonspear...  Ye would like it enhanced?~
@295 = ~I can reforge and strengthen it with some illithium ore, If'n ye can manage to find any not already claimed by one of the holier-than-thou types from the temple district.~
@296 = ~Ye have all the illithium we need here, now just the matter of me commission.  A simple sum of 8,000gp and I will make this holy blade truly shine for ye.~
@297 = ~The holy blade of the Asters?   Not an easy task to improve it further, but certainly not impossible....~
@298 = ~I need a gemstone filled with holy power, the legendary Eye of Tyr would work.  Problem is finding it, heh.  But that's something for an adventurer like yerself to solve.  Find it and bring it back to me shop, and I'll create a blade that will make the beasties flee from the sight of it.~
@299 = ~*Rolls the Eye of Tyr around in his palm*

Bloody hells... this is the Eye of Tyr, to be sure.  If ye can see to part with 8,000 gold coins, I will fit this to yer holy longsword.~
@300 = ~Really nice piece of paladin's headgear ye have here friend, such a sad story behind it.  Ye would like it enhanced?~
@301 = ~Aye, I can improve upon this circlet for ye.  I would need a couple of ioun stones of wisdom, one of silver and one of incandescent blue would make this legendary helm a true boon to those who specialize in the divine.~
@302 = ~*tosses the silver and incandescent blue ioun stones in the air and catches both in a single swipe*

These two stones are perfect for yer circlet.  I only need 5,000gp for the commission, and your help at me forge for the day.~
@303 = ~The craftsmanship on this shield is magnificient, rivals some of me own work, heh.  You want it improved, aye?~
@304 = ~We can improve this angelic shield of yers.  Find and bring me a pearly white ioun stone and some elven holy water, and I'll set to work on 'er.~
@305 = ~Ahh, ye've the stone and holy water I need here.  Now just the matter of me commission.  3,500 gold coins, what ye say?~
@306 = ~Nice handiwork on this chain, appears to be of elven make, and has some years of use to it, to be sure.~
@307 = ~I can rework this blessed chainmail by reinforcing it with plates, but I'll need a special metal to do it justice.  I've heard tales of ore from the heavens itself.  If ye find some of this starfall ore, I can use it to enhance your hallowed mail.~
@308 = ~Ah, spectacular sheen to this ore ye brought me, surely this must be from the heavens.  I can use this to forge you a suit of plate fit for the pure of heart.  5,000gp for me commission and it's a done deal.~
@309 = ~Looks here like ye've been exterminating some eight-legged vermin recently.  Good on ye!  I cannae stand the creepers meself, but I can craft ye a nice garment from the silks if ye have enough.~
@310 = ~I'll need four swaths of giant spider silks to have enough to weave into a protective garment for ye, it'll be light enough even for an acrobat, hah!~
@311 = ~Ye've got enough silk here, all that remains is me commission.  3,500 gold and I can start immediately for ye.~
@312 = ~*swings the Blazing Glory +3 about*

This morningstar has surely seen it's share of battles, aye?  I can almost hear the beat of war drums just by holding it.~
@313 = ~Enhance this morningstar?  Aye, I can do it for ye, I'll need a few things tae do it.  A wand of the heavens, a scroll of flame strike, and an elemental gemstone of fire.  Bring me these and I will reforge yer morningstar into a weapon fit for Tempus himself.~
@314 = ~Ye've all I need here to reforge this morningstar of battles.  If ye can spare a day's worth of yer help at me forge and 7,500 gold coins, we can seal the deal.~
@315 = ~Aye, ye've collected the scales of a shadow dragon. By the Soul Forger, 'tis a grand sight.  I'm sure the deathly beast waylaid many an adventurer before ye came along, no doubt.  I can make ye a fine suit of heavy plate, lightweight scale, a protective helm, or even a sturdy shield from yon scales, if ye like.~
@316 = ~Ah! Scales from a red dragon, a beast of the Dread Flame.  I can make ye an exquisite suit of heavy plate, lightweight scale, a protective helm, or even a sturdy shield.  Do any of these hold yer interest?~
@317 = ~Fair enough, what else?~
@318 = ~'Tis a pity, anything else?~
@319 = ~I can use the Nypmh's Tear to complete your oaken ring.~
@320 = ~Ah, bloody hells, these be scales of a noble silver dragon!  Tell me ya dinnae slay one yerself to get these?  Bah, it be no matter of import, we surely aren't going to let these go to waste!~
@321 = ~I can forge for ye a truly magnificent suit of heavy plate, lightweight scale armor, a sturdy shield, or a protective helm from these scales.  Ye will be protected by any of them well enough, though some folk will look down upon ye fer wearing it, heh.~
@322 = ~I would need 5,000 gold coins and yer help at me forge.  That lazy Duergar apprentice of mine refuses to return to work.  *spits*~
@323 = ~Another scale from a beastie, aye?  Ye be proficent at slayin the wily creatures, to be sure.~
@324 = ~Ye've here the scales of a white dragon, still cold to the touch!  I can forge for ye a splendid suit of heavy plate, lightweight scale armor, a sturdy shield, or even a protective helm from yon scales.  Any of those pique yer interest?~
@325 = ~A mere 5,000 gold coins, and yer strong arm at me bellows again for the day.  What say ye?~
@326 = ~Ah, ye've some scales of a great blue dragon here, a terrible thunder lizard to be sure.  Must still have some electrical charge left in these, the hair on me arm be standing up straight just from holding 'em.~
@327 = ~From these azure scales, I can forge for ye an exquisite suit of heavy plate, light scale armor, sturdy shield, or a protective helmet, what say ye?~
@328 = ~5,000 gold pieces and a day's worth of time at me forge to complete the work.~
@329 = ~Ey?  I know this hammer... it once belonged to that rat-bastard Durn Coldhearth.  Betrayed his clan, and if that wasn't bad enough, made a deal with a lich to become one himself!~
@330 = ~Improve Coldhearth's hammer?  Aye, certainly possible.  I would need an artifact from a powerful lich, a tooth would work best.  Bring one to me shop and I will reforge your traitor's hammer with it's power.~
@331 = ~Ye've got a lich's tooth?  One from a drow lich, no less.  This will work for your hammer.  5,000 gold pieces to seal the deal and I will get started on it.~
@332 = ~Ah, yer corrosive dagger again eh?  Ye wish it more powerful?~
@333 = ~It would take a mighty powerful gem to enhance this dagger further.  Bring me the Eye of Ichor and 5,000gp, and I'll reforge yer dagger into the finest ye've seen.~
@334 = ~Ah, this is the Eye of Ichor alright, and will do nicely.   Ye've the gold as well, it seems.  Shall I get started?~
@335 = ~What've ye brought me here.... Ah, a battle axe from the Ice Dragon Berserker Lodge, quite rare in these parts.~
@336 = ~Hmmm, hard to improve on this axe, but anything is possible, with the right components.  To improve upon this axe, I will need a wand of frost, a scroll of ice storm, and most importantly, the legendary Frostreaver.~
@337 = ~Excellent!  Ye've found the Frostreaver, and ye've the scroll and wand here too.  A simple matter of 10,000 gold coins for me commission and I'll reforge yer beserker axe into something special.~
@338 = ~The Blizzard Axe, has she been serving ye well?  Improved ye say?  Hmmm...~
@339 = ~Yes, there be a way, only one.  An elemental gemstone of coldest ice, the Soul of Frost.  If ye find it in yer travels, bring it back to me shop.~
@340 = ~I felt the chill as soon as ye entered, ye've found the Soul of Frost.  For a mere 5,000 crowns I will use this to bring the full force of winter to yer axe.~ 
@341 = ~Ah, ye've got a nice bear pelt here, good quality if I do say so meself.~
@342 = ~I can make a fine pair of boots out of this pelt for ye.  Any dwarf worth his salt knows the value of a good pair of boots, some of us even consider them lucky, heh.  2,000 gold, ye interested?~
@343 = ~Ey, I know this hammer, Lady Ashideena's namesake!  Such fine craftsmanship and history behind this one.~
@344 = ~I can reforge this hammer into something that would make Lady Ashideena proud, I just need a few things from ye.  I will need ye to bring me a wand of lightning, a scroll of lightning bolt, and most importantly, I'll need ye to find and bring me Borok's Fist.~
@345 = ~Ye've everything I need to reforge Ashideena, a simple manner of my comission is all that remains.  5,000 gold pieces, no less.  Shall we begin?~  
@346 = ~Ah, ye've brought me Ashideena again.  Further enhanced ye say?  Aye, I can do it.~
@347 = ~To empower Ashideena further, I'll need an elemental gemstone, the Breath of Wind.~
@348 = ~Ye've the Breath of Wind here, I can use this to enchance the Ashideena with.  It will cost ye 10,000 pieces o' gold.  What say ye?~  
