@8000 = ~You have known us for so short a time, and yet you have bought our freedom with blood. My child, my friend, it is a debt I can never repay...  Please, take this as a token of our unending gratitude.  A disconsolate skald with an insatiable penchant for drink and women left it behind when he came through some months ago.  He was not a good fit for our troupe, but perhaps his helmet will be as such for you.~ [RAELIS21]
@8001 = ~I say this because I've grown rather fond of this playhouse and would like to make you an offer for it.  I have a magical flute in my possession that will undoubtedly be useful to you in your travels.~
@8002 = ~My heart is free, and I have you to thank. With the creature gone, my lands are free, and the dead that fell before you are avenged. I thank you as they would.  I found this helmet in the remains of their camp, I think they would be pleased that you have and use it towards righteous ends.~ [GARREN08]
@8003 = ~Your honor and my child are restored. I thank you. The creature lives; I will not rest easy at night, but I have my child and I could not ask for more than that.  Please, take this helmet that I found in the remains of the paladin's camp, I think they would be pleased for you to have it and use in good health.~
@8004 = ~Did I promise that? Well, mate, here you go... somethin' even better for yer honesty, an' thanks to you for a deed well done. Anything ye need in the future, don't be hesitating to look me up.~
@8005 = ~You continue to be a fine resource for the Morninglord. Your service has been exemplary, and you have earned your place within the temple order.  We recently liberated this shield of the ancient family of Egon from a shadow thief attempting to fence it.  I am certain the morninglord would be pleased for you to have it.~
@8006 = ~High Watcher Oisig was correct in recommending you. You are an asset to Helm. I thank you on behalf of the Morninglord.  Please, take this shield as a token of our gratitude, it is from the ancient family of Egon and will serve you well in your travels.~
@8007 = ~Your service has been exceptional. I wish you were a member of our temple. You would have been a fine cleric had your life taken another path. As a token of our thanks, please take this.  We liberated this shield from a shadow thief fence.  It hails from the ancient family of Egon and will serve you well.~
@8008 = ~And now they are to be married... what wonderful news. Thank you again, my <LADYLORD>. I cannot express my gratitude enough for everything you have done here.  Before you came to Trademeet, I had purchased these for my son, thinking they would help him if he were to run off foolhardily after Raissa.  Thanks to you, he didn't have to, and I believe my <LORDLADY>ship would find them most useful.~
@8009 = ~Yes, thank you so much. *sniff* Please, take this as a token of our thanks for bringing peace to our son.  It was to be a gift for him, and I can no longer bear to look at it.  Come, my husband... let us go home.~
@8010 = ~As I knew you would be.  For your first reward in my service, I offer this armor.  This one sought to usurp me in ages past.  I can think of no better fate for him as you cut a bloody swath across Faerûn in my name.~
@8011 = ~This is my last act of service to you, pig. I'll see you in the Abyss!~
@8012 = ~I... I thank you! You have rescued a perfect stranger and... and asked for nothing in return. Certainly a selfless act if ever I have heard of one.  Please, take these old boots, I'll not need them anymore as after this, I am quite done with adventuring. Thank you once again, I will speak kind of your name to all whom ask!~
@8013 = ~<CHARNAME>! I have received news that you have cleared out the Firewine Bridge ruins! No longer will kobolds plague our tiny village. I must congratulate you on a job well done. Everyone is grateful for your help. Take these boots I found exploring the ruins long ago as a show of our gratitude.~
@8014 = ~And what if it was? It is not of my making. I myself was once a resident for a time. It tends to snag passing teleporting mages from time to time. I left my magics and gadgets and was able to use some minor incantations to escape. Passive resistance is more successful when the very ground seems to drag magic to it. The others might find their release if they lose the anger and attachment to their toys. Ah, I will not argue this with you, the place was not of my making. You have done well enough to earn this. Goodbye.~
@8015 = ~You return. You are proven capable, at least in this respect. Certainly you have the will to change your personal ways as well. We are square and fair, for the moment. I cannot guarantee that we will remain so, however, as your kind is to be scrutinized closely. Rather a nonexistent short-term memory as well, I'm afraid. You have done me a favor, now do yourself one. Behave yourself until you are of positive standing in the community, and take this, I've no longer any need for it. Begone.~
@8016 = ~Surely it cannae be?  Is that shimmering piece o' carapace ye have there from a Remorhaz?  How did ye manage to find such a horrid beast in these parts, much less slay it?!  No matter, if ye are willing to part with it, I will happily pay a tidy sum of 2,000 gold for it.  When I was but a wee lad, I once saw a fearsome helmet made from a remorhaz shell and I would like to try me own hand at making one.~
@8017 = ~Ah, this will make a right-kingly helm, may even turn aside a spell or two.  Something this exotic may even draw the eye of Entar Silvershield, heh!  I thank you, <CHARNAME>. My smithy will surive this iron shortage yet.~
@8018 = ~Hells, a terrible shame. To work with something so exotic and rare would have been a real pleasure, and bring much needed coin to my smithy.  Hmmm, <CHARNAME>, an offer for ye, if you'll hear it.  For 6,000 gold, I will make a fine helm with it for you.  Less than my usual fare for such a piece, but I could use the work.~
@8019 = ~Ye be short on gold?  Since your party is obviously battle-hardened enough to slay a remorhaz, ye may want to try your luck in exploring the ruins of Durlag's tower.  It be a deadly place, for sure, but such places tend to be rich in artifacts and gold as well.~
@8020 = ~Then a deal is struck!  Curing and working with such material will take some time, but once finished, you will have a helm that even the grand dukes would envy.  Come back after five days, and it will be ready for you.~
@8021 = ~Only for you, <CHARNAME>.~
@8022 = ~Ah, you have returned. And here be the helm I promised you. Enchanting, isn't it? A finer helmet I've never made. Wear it well.~
@8023 = ~A tickle more running than I care to do in a dragon's age! Such is the way o' the nightsneak, but not another profession pays as well. Ye be quite the force under the weight o' pursuit, grabbin' the pretties while hoofin' it fast! Ye prove to me an' brethren all that ye be here for good reason. Here be yer reward, ye've earned it, and tonight we'll suck the monkey a keg apiece tavern wise!~
@8024 = ~Well snuck, by any measure! Gantolandan wakes this morn none the wiser, but more the poorer! All the guild will hear o' this, and ye be welcomed as brethren. Here be yer reward, ye've earned it, and tonight we'll suck the monkey a keg apiece tavern-wise!~
@8025 = ~AAAAAAGH!~
@8026 = ~For Tempus!~
@8027 = ~Blood and death!~
@8028 = ~I shall join my kin in glorious death!~
@8029 = ~** THE BHAAL CHILD WISHES MORE POWER...  PREDICTABLE AND BORING.  DRINK OF THIS THEN, EVIL ONE, AND SATE YOUR LUST FOR MORE POWER.  I WILL FEAST ON EGGS OF HATED SILVER THIS NIGHT. **~
@8030 = ~Primes!  They must have a way out!  Take the ore and kill them all!~
@8031 = ~** AHHH, MORE PRIMES FOR THE SLAVE PENS, COME THEN, SO THAT I MAY BREAK YOU. **~
@8032 = ~Hurry!, while the demon is distracted!~
@8033 = ~RAAAARHH! To freedom!~
@8034 = ~One of the shadow gems you were carrying begins to hum with power absorbed from within the Shadow Plane~
@8035 = ~Join us in darknesssssss....~
@8036 = ~*plays an instrument*~
@8037 = ~Ah, I'm so glad I can move home again. Bentley is a kindly man but it is always best not to push favors too far.  He gave me this nice pair of boots, but they chafe me something horrible, and I much rather have these old boots back anyway.  Maybe these new boots will be a better fit for ye, they're all yours.  If you have any of my other possessions, come talk to me again.~ 
@8038 = ~Thank you. Thank you for bringing me the news.  Please, take this for your troubles.  Joseph gave this to me as a gift just before going back into those damned mines, and I can bear to look at it no longer.~
@8039 = ~I care nothing for the drow war on the surface elves, and I spit on Phaere and her House. I can give this extra copy of the eggs to you to foil her plans, and should things go awry, take this cloak as well.  I took it from some foolish Duergar who attempted to ambush me in the tunnels.~
