@2235 = ~Cromwell's Remorhaz Shell Helm~
@2236 = ~Shortly after opening his shop in Athkatla, a fishmonger fleeing from Easthaven happend upon Cromwell's forge.  The fishmonger brought with him several chitinous Remorhaz shells, and told of destruction of his hometown by a horde of monsters commanded by what had been a seemingly harmless shop owner that lived in the town.  He requested Cromwell to forge him a suit of armor made from the shells so that he could return home to face the shopkeeper-mage who had betrayed his neighbors.  Unfortunately, the fishmonger could not afford the commission.  Not wanting to send away someone in such dire need, Cromwell agreed to make the armor if the fishmonger would allow him to keep a small portion of shell for himself.  Cromwell then used the shell to forge a new helmet for himself, as he knew it would provide greater protection against magical misfires at his forge.   No one knows what ever happened to the fishmonger or the unique suit of Remorhaz armor, it is most likely he was waylaid by bandits on his return trip and the armor stolen.

